NetworkManager: NetworkManager (D-Bus/HAL-based network management)
NetworkManager: Networking on Linux right now is painful for the mobile
NetworkManager: desktop user, especially in comparison to other operating
NetworkManager: systems. A laptop user should never need to use the command
NetworkManager: line or configuration files to manage their network; it
NetworkManager: should "Just Work" as automatically as possible and intrude
NetworkManager: as little as possible into the user's workflow. NetworkManager
NetworkManager: attempts to make networking invisible.
